{Speech 3}{}{This is the "Last Gasp," a saloon and funeral parlor. Full-service operation. Our motto is "Into the grave with a bottle."}
{Speech 3 Answer 4}{}{That's a mighty awkward combination, Josh.}
{Speech 3 Answer 13}{}{Yeah, Josh, Lucretia Borgia would be proud of you.}
{Speech 3 Answer 14}{}{What does it take to buy a coffin?}
{Speech 3 Answer 15}{}{How do I arrange a funeral?}
{Speech 3 Answer 13*}{}{From now on I'll steer clear of your "gin from the tap."}
{Speech 4}{}{That's right. But I couldn't make ends meet if I just buried people - a dead business, so to speak. Oh, it was a matter of life and death. So I rebuilt my place so it serves drinks too.}
{Speech 4 Answer 2}{}{Uh-huh. I'm almost afraid to ask you anything else. But I'll try anyway.}
{Speech 4 Answer 5}{}{Uh, doesn't all this scenery ruin people's appetite?}
{Speech 4 Answer Exit}{}{I don't think I can take another pun. Goodbye. }
{Speech 5}{}{Well, if everything here were real, then maybe. But it's not real. At least, not all of it. Besides, the miners actually like it. They feel lucky to be alive at all.}
{Speech 5 Answer 6}{}{This is all creepy. You're a very unbalanced man.}
{Speech 5 Answer 2}{}{I see. Then I guess I'll ask you about something else.}
{Speech 5 Answer Exit}{}{I suppose some folks might appreciate it. But not me. It gives me the creeps. I'm leaving.}
{Speech 6}{}{Creepy? Unbalanced? I've been told that savages eat their dead.}
{Speech 6 Answer 7}{}{Well, how else could we grok their essence?}
{Speech 6 Answer 8}{}{Come on now. We cook them first. We're not completely wild, after all.}
{Speech 6 Answer 11}{}{What nonsense. Who told you that?}
{Speech 7}{}{Damn Martians. And here I almost took you for a savage. Aren't I a fool? Still, the way I see it, cannibalism is cannibalism. }
{Speech 7 Answer 8}{}{Come on now. We cook them first. We're not completely wild, after all.}
{Speech 8}{}{Well, if you don't eat them raw... No, wait just a minute. It's still cannibalism! You're real filth, even for a savage.}
{Speech 8 Answer 9}{}{Cool it, Josh. I'm just kidding. Heh-heh. Damn, we just cook their parts.}
{Speech 9}{}{Parts, huh? And which parts exactly?}
{Speech 9 Answer 10}{}{Who cares? (you shrug). Parts are just parts.}
{Speech 9 Answer 12}{}{I'm just pulling your leg, Josh. Let me ask you about something else instead.}
{Speech 10}{}{Well, I suppose that makes sense.}
{Speech 10 Answer 2}{}{Of course it does. Let me ask you about something else.}
{Speech 10 Answer Exit}{}{Speaking of which, I'm getting hungry. See you soon, Josh. Bye.}
{Speech 11}{}{Honestly, I don't know. But it's the gospel truth. Why else would you file your teeth down? Eh? Answer me, would you?}
{Speech 11 Answer 2}{}{I don't file them. Fine, never mind. Let me ask you something else instead.}
{Speech 12}{}{Let go of my tail, you cannibal! You found it, even though I didn't know I had one. I'm going to need it for a long while yet. Find yourself another one!}
{Speech 12 Answer 2}{}{All right, all right! What's with you! I'm joking, heh-heh. Let me just ask you about something else.}
{Speech 12 Answer Exit}{}{All right, I'll go take a walk. But if I don't find anything better, I'll be back. See you. Goodbye.}
{Speech 12 Answer 31}{}{About the wanamingo}
{Speech 13}{}{How am I supposed to take that?}
{Speech 13 Answer 4}{}{I mean it comes out very... um... an unusual combination.}
{Speech 13 Answer 2}{}{Nothing. Never mind, Josh. Let me ask you something.}
{Speech 14}{}{First you have to kick the bucket. You aren't planning on playing those games anytime soon, are you?}
{Speech 14 Answer 2}{}{Mm. No buckets. Let me ask you something.}
{Speech 14 Answer Exit}{}{Maybe I'll just help someone else play it. Goodbye, Josh.}
{Speech 15}{}{Well, to start with you need to strangle somebody. But Sheriff Marion doesn't approve of that sort of thing. So I don't recommend it.}
{Speech 15 Answer 2}{}{I'll keep myself in check. Can I ask you something else, Josh?}
{Speech 15 Answer Exit}{}{Got it. At least I'll know who to turn to if some "accident" happens. Goodbye.}
