{Speech 16 Answer Exit}{}{Here's the money. }
{Speech 16 Answer 2}{}{I've kind of lost the urge. Let me ask something else instead.}
{Speech 17}{}{Very generous of you. To send a greeting to everyone - it all comes to 50 coins. Hey, turns out I'm a poet.}
{Speech 17 Answer Exit}{}{Oh, those puns will be the death of me, Josh. Just a friendly warning. Here's the money.}
{Speech 17 Answer 2}{}{Hmm. That pun seems to have killed the urge. Can I ask you something else?}
{Speech 18}{}{Well, not much that would concern me. Mostly I run a quiet business. Quiet as the grave, you might say.}
{Speech 18 Answer 2}{}{I've got you figured out. I've got a few more questions.}
{Speech 18 Answer Exit}{}{All right, I'm out of here. Bye.}
{Speech 19}{}{Get out of here before you mess up the floor.@@What brought you here?@@Move along, move along. You moron!@@This place isn't for you.@@Get lost.}
{Speech 20}{}{[Warily] And what sort of questions? I've got a license to sell liquor, ask the sheriff!}
{Speech 20 Answer 21}{}{The license has nothing to do with it. Have you noticed anything unusual around here lately?}
{Speech 21}{}{What? What was I supposed to notice? I don't get it. And anyway, what the hell are you doing playing detective here?}
{Speech 21 Answer 22}{}{I'm carrying out a personal request from the sheriff. If you've got questions, take them up with him.}
{Speech 22}{}{Oh, the sheriff's involved? Well then go ahead, ask away.}
{Speech 22 Answer 23}{}{I'll repeat, have you noticed anything strange around here? The thing is, some of the townsfolk claim they've seen a wanamingo. I'm looking for witnesses.}
{Speech 23}{}{SEEN it? Are you sure they saw a LIVE wanamingo? [The barkeep turns pale]}
{Speech 23 Answer 24}{}{Well, hmm, not so much that anyone saw one in the flesh. Nobody's seen one yet, it seems. But they've heard their roar and other strange sounds.}
{Speech 24}{}{ Ha! [The barkeep visibly perks up] You almost scared me. Heard them, well, I've got my suspicions about who heard them, heh-heh.}
{Speech 24 Answer 25}{}{Who do you mean? The widow Rooney?}
{Speech 25}{}{[He looks like the barkeep is suppressing a chuckle] Urp! No! I was thinking of someone else.}
{Speech 25 Answer 26}{}{And why are you so amused? Well, have you seen anything?}
{Speech 26}{}{Of course I've seen something! Just go take a look at the cemetery yourself. There are three fresh graves dug up there. Who'd be digging them up if not the wanamingo?}
{Speech 26 Answer 27}{}{Well, could be anyone.}
{Speech 27}{}{I live right nearby, I'd have seen everything. But as it is, I only hear those creatures gnashing their teeth at night and stomping off somewhere into town.}
{Speech 27 Answer 28}{}{Did you see it with your own eyes?}
{Speech 28}{}{It happened. Just a glimpse, though. Thank God I managed to shut the door.}
{Speech 28 Answer 29}{}{Maybe it was a rat, or a resident of Redding?}
{Speech 29}{}{It was dark, I could've been mistaken. But I'm sure it wasn't a rat and it wasn't a person. It was something huge and terrifying! A wanamingo! I'm telling you for sure!}
{Speech 29 Answer 30}{}{Hmm. All right. All the accounts check out. Thanks for the help.}
{Speech 30}{}{ Heh, don't mention it. You all there, come on, get some protection set up for me quick. Or they'll eat me!}
{Speech 30 Answer Exit}{}{Don't leave the house at night. If you notice anything else, come straight to me, or the sheriff.}
{Speech 31}{}{Ha, howdy! I'm glad you came by! I saw three more wanamingo! They were stealing whiskey from my storeroom!}
{Speech 31 Answer 32}{}{Shut your trap, blabbermouth! I'm not falling for your lies anymore.}
{Speech 32}{}{[Backs away, stunned] Hey, what's with you! I'm trying to help! You asked me to yourself!}
{Speech 32 Answer 33}{}{Shut up. I've been told what you get up to at night, and the wanamingo have nothing to do with it.}
{Speech 33}{}{Who told you?! What did they tell you?!}
{Speech 33 Answer 34}{}{Never mind. What's that stone with the rope over there under the table?}
{Speech 34}{}{What stone?!}
{Speech 34 Answer 35}{}{QUIET now! Quit playing the fool. I know everything. How you torment that poor widow. And right now I'm wondering whether to finish you off on the spot.}
{Speech 35}{}{[Falls to his knees] Nooo! Don't kill me! I didn't do anything wrong! It was a joke! A harmless joke! I just got drunk and started acting crazy!}
{Speech 35 Answer 36}{}{Be quiet. I won't touch you. Not worth dirtying my hands. But I'll tell the sheriff. Hand over that stone.}
{Speech 36}{}{Oh, thank you! I won't do it again! Never!}
{Speech 36 Answer Exit}{}{You watch yourself. If Rooney complains about noises one more time, you'll be in big trouble.}
